    • Method Detail

      • receivedResponse

        boolean receivedResponse(java.lang.Object response,
                         boolean didLoadFromCache,
                         APIRequest request,
                         java.lang.Object tag)
        Called when the APIRequest received a response. Based on the ResponseType of the APIRequest the type of response is determined.
        Parameters:
        response - The response. If responseType is JSON, this is a JSONObject If responseType is PLAIN_TEXT, this is a String If responseType is RAW_DATA, this is an InputStream which will be closed after this method is called.
        didLoadFromCache - Whether or not the response is loaded from the cache
        request - The APIRequest which has been executed.
        tag - The custom tag given to the request
        Returns:
        Whether or not the response was valid or not. If the responses success is false or contains corrupt data, return false. If the response is usable, return true.
